docs {
  Fetch one tenant by id. Requires `business:read`.
  
  The response includes the resolved location relations (`country`, `state`,
  `city`, `area`) — each `{ id, name, … }` or `null` — alongside the tenant's
  own fields (`shortName`, `addressLine`, `pincode`, `countryId`/`stateId`/
  `cityId`/`areaId`, `logoUrl`, `photoUrl`), so the UI can render location
  labels without extra lookups.
  
  Audit fields: `createdBy` / `updatedBy` (SiteAdmin user ids of the creator /
  last editor), their resolved display names `createdByName` / `updatedByName`,
  and `createdAt` / `updatedAt`. `updatedBy` is set on every tenant edit
  (including suspend/reactivate).
}
